quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,27,"And Allah intendeth to relent toward you, and those that follow lusts intend that ye shall incline a mighty inclining"
  4,28,"Allah intendeth that he shall lighten unto you, and man hath been created weak"
  4,29,"O Ye who believe! devour not your substance among yourselves unlawfully, but let it be a trading among you by mutual agreement. And slay not yourselves, verily Allah is unto you ever Merciful"
  4,30,"And whosoever doth that in transgression- and wrong, presently We shall roast him in Fire; and with Allah that is ever easy"
  4,31,"If ye shun the grievous sins from which ye are prohibited, We shall expiate from you your misdeeds, and make you enter a noble Entrance"
  4,32,"And long not for that wherewith Allah hath preferred one of you above anot her Unto men shall be the portion of that which they earn, and unto women shall be the portion of that which they earn. And ask Allah for some of His grace, verily Allah is of everything Knower"
  4,33,"And unto each We have appointed inheritors of that which the parents or the near of kin leave behind, and unto those with whom ye have made your pledges give their portion. Verily Allah is ever of everything a Witness"